Countries around the world, both friendly and hostile to Irans' Islamic government, sent  help to Iran where 40,000 people died in the earthquake Thursday.
The United States  expressed its willingness to help and Iran said it would welcome aid from the Red Cross  and other U.S. humanitarian groups.
Moderate Arab countries-- Egypt, Saudi Arabia,  and Jordan--offered help as did Italy, France, West Germany, the Vatican, India,  China, Poland and Malaysia.
The Soviet republic of Armenia flew a professional  lifesaving team to Iran on Saturday.
Iran's neighbor, Soviet Azerbaijan, sent tons of  food and contributed more than $500,000 to a special earthquake fund. 
